&lt;h2 id=&#34;problem&#34;&gt;Problem
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;tkinter.Text&lt;/code&gt; calls to &lt;code&gt;edit_undo()&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;edit_redo()&lt;/code&gt; have no effect.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;analysis&#34;&gt;Analysis
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;This occurs because the &lt;code&gt;undo&lt;/code&gt; parameter of &lt;code&gt;Text&lt;/code&gt; is not set to &lt;code&gt;True&lt;/code&gt;. Only after setting this can &lt;code&gt;edit_undo()&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;edit_redo()&lt;/code&gt; be &amp;ldquo;activated&amp;rdquo;.&lt;br&gt;
This error is difficult to detect since it doesn&amp;rsquo;t throw an error message. Discovered after extensive research&amp;hellip;&lt;br&gt;
Hope the Python official team can improve this aspect in the future.&lt;/p&gt;
